<CO>
   BEI AICP ACAT CFSB CRII HHRD JSBF SOSI SWFT VDMK KEC GOVO
</CO>
<IN>
SECURITIES INDUSTRY (SCR)
STOCK MARKET, OFFERINGS (STK)
</IN>
<LP>
   NEW YORK -- The New York Stock Exchange announced one new
listing and the American Stock Exchange announced an initial
public offering, while the Pacific Stock Exchange added one
listing and the National Market System of the
over-the-counter market announced nine initial public
offerings.
                                                                                                       

</LP>
<TEXT>
   Kent Electronics Corp., a Houston producer of custom-made
electronics will begin trading on the Big Board on Friday
under the symbol KNT. It previously traded on the Amex.
                                                                                                       

   Benchmark Electronics Inc., a Clute, Texas, electronics
manufacturing services company, began trading last week on
the Amex as an initial public offering under BEI.
                                                                                                       

   Go-Video Inc., a Scottsdale, Ariz. maker of dual-deck
videocassette recorders, joined the Pacific Stock Exchange in
May and began trading under GVI. Go-Video also trades on the
over-the-counter market.
                                                                                                       

   Joining the OTC market, AICorp Inc., a Waltham, Mass.,
maker of computer-aided software engineering products, began
trading under AICP. Arctco Inc., a Thief River Falls, Minn.,
maker of snowmobiles and related accessories, began trading
under ACAT. CFSB Bancorp Inc., a Lansing, Mich., bank holding
company for Capitol Federal, began trading under CFSB. Crest
Industries Inc, a Miami Fla., distributor of home improvement
products, began trading under CRII. Horsehead Resource
Development Co., a Palmerton, Pa., hazardous waste recovery
company, began trading under HHRD. JSB Financial Inc., a
Lynbrook, N.Y., holding company for Jamaica Savings Bank,
FSB, began trading under JSBF. Sundowner Offshore Services
Inc., a Houston oil and gas well services company, began
trading under SOSI. Swift Transportation Co., a Phoenix
holding company for Swift Transportation and Cooper Motor
Lines, truckload carriers, began trading under SWFT. Vidmark
Inc., a Santa Monica, Calif., distributor of motion pictures,
began trading under VDMK.
</TEXT>
