<CO>
   EUROP
</CO>
<LP>
   FRANKFURT, West Germany -- West German wholesale sales in
May rose a real, or inflation-adjusted, 7% from a year
earlier, the government said.
   Nominal sales also increased 7% from a year earlier,
reflecting the steadiness of wholesale prices during the
year.
</LP>
