<HL>
   Marketing &amp; Media:
   News Corp. Sale to G.P. Group
</HL>
<DATE>
07/02/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE B5
</SO>
<CO>
   NWS
</CO>
<IN>
TENDER OFFERS, MERGERS, ACQUISITIONS (TNM)
MEDIA, PUBLISHING, BROADCASTING, ELECTRONIC PUBLISHING (MED)
</IN>
<LP>
   NEW YORK -- News Corp. said it completed the sale of Star
magazine to G.P. Group Inc., publisher of the National
Enquirer and Weekly World News, for $400 million.
   The publishing and broadcasting concern said it will
receive $200 million in cash and $200 million in convertible
preferred stock in G.P. Group, based in Lantana, Fla. G.P.
Group is owned by principals of New York-based Macfadden
Holdings Inc. and Boston Ventures Limited Partnership.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   The National Enquirer is the nation's largest supermarket
tabloid, with circulation of about four million; the Star's
circulation is about 3.5 million.
</TEXT>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO>
WSJ900702-0155
</DOCNO>
<DOCID>
900702-0155.
</DOCID>
<HL>
   Siebe Commences Offer
</HL>
<DATE>
07/02/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE A2
</SO>
<CO>
   U.SEB FOX
</CO>
<IN>
TENDER OFFERS, MERGERS, ACQUISITIONS (TNM)
</IN>
<LP>
   BOSTON -- Siebe PLC said it commenced a previously
announced tender offer for all outstanding shares of Foxboro
Co.'s common stock at $52 a share.
   The offer, scheduled to expire July 27, is subject to the
tender of at least two-thirds of the outstanding shares, on a
fully diluted basis.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   Siebe PLC is a British company that manufactures
industrial and environmental controls, specialized
engineerings, safety and life support products.
   On June 25, Siebe agreed to buy Foxboro Co., the
Massachusetts-based company that produces process controls
for manufacturing.
</TEXT>
