   Whittle takes in about $40 million a year in advertising
from the magazines and hopes to double the revenue with the
addition of the TV show, which will have an hour-long format
divided into eight segments on family issues and be updated
every two weeks on videodisk.
   A spokeswoman for ABC, a unit of Capital Cities/ABC Inc.,
New York, said Ms. Lunden recently signed a new five-year
contract for "Good Morning America."
